# Why We Are Raising Capital

The objective of this pre-seed round is not simply to accelerate software development.

It is to build the computational infrastructure required to operate BCSentinel as a continuously running institutional intelligence platform.

The next stage of development requires dedicated computing infrastructure capable of continuously analysing blockchain activity, executing empirical investigation pipelines and generating institutional intelligence in near real time.

Capital will primarily be allocated to:

## Dedicated Infrastructure

Deployment of dedicated computing nodes capable of running the complete BCSentinel intelligence pipeline continuously.

This includes blockchain infrastructure, high-performance computing resources and enterprise-grade storage required to support long-term empirical monitoring.

---

## Computational Capacity

Ethereum currently generates several million on-chain transactions every day.

BCSentinel is being engineered to continuously analyse a strategically selected subset of these transactions rather than the entire blockchain.

The target operational capacity is to investigate approximately **60,000 to 120,000 transactions per day**, prioritised through the platform's Discovery Engine and empirical filtering methodology.

This selective approach focuses computational resources on the transactions most likely to contain evidence of emerging digital economic formation processes.

---

## Artificial Intelligence Infrastructure

Expand the platform's AI capabilities through more capable reasoning models dedicated to:

• evidence interpretation

• institutional report generation

• entity attribution

• knowledge extraction

• continuous library expansion

AI is intended to augment empirical investigation rather than replace it.

Strategic decisions and platform evolution remain under human supervision.

---

## Continuous Monitoring

Transition from historical reconstruction to permanent institutional monitoring.

Dedicated infrastructure will allow BCSentinel to operate continuously, identifying, investigating and documenting emerging formation processes as they develop.

---

## Platform Engineering

Complete the transition from research platform to production-grade institutional software.

This includes scalability, security, monitoring infrastructure, enterprise deployment and client-facing capabilities.

---

The objective of this investment is to transform BCSentinel from a validated research platform into a continuously operating institutional intelligence infrastructure.

